  , issueCommentBody =
      "@rclai are you trying to filter the changefeed to only include documents where `id`, `b`, or `c` have changed? If so the workaround is a bit more involved than what @mlucy suggested. I've wanted to do the same thing before (see #3099). Here's what I've used:\r\n\r\n```js\r\nvar fields = r.expr([ 'id', 'b', 'c' ]);\r\nr.table('cities').get(...).changes().filter(function (row) {\r\n  return fields.contains(function (field) {\r\n    // compare the fields we care about\r\n    return row('new_val')(field).ne(row('old_val')(field)).default(true);\r\n  })\r\n})\r\n```"
  , issueCommentId = 104795695
